records.addlTxt:
Counsel waived.
NO CONTEST pleas entered to counts 1 and 2, negligent handling of burning materials and disorderly conduct.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 3.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for eighteen (18) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) No contact with Revolutions Bar;
2) Pay restitution of $1,000.00 to Dana and Debbie Rohr, 1730 Ahrens Court, Manitowoc, WI at the rate of $50.00 per month;
3) Maintain absolute sobriety;
4) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) AODA assessment and follow through;
6) Undergo a psychological assessment at the agents discretion;
7) Maintain fulltime employment or work search;
8) Pay court costs;
9) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
10) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
11) spend thirty (30) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 1 only, stayed and to be imposed at the agents discretion and upon order of the court.
Expungement is ordered under Section 973.015 upon successful completion of the sentence.  The Court finds that the defendant will benefit and society will not be harmed by expungment in this matter.
Minutes.
